abstract_ssm: John Everett Watts, Jr. (1930-1982) was a composer, teacher and advocate of "new" and electronic music. He also enjoyed forays into literary composition and journalism, and worked closely with his third wife, Laura Foreman, on dance and performance art pieces. The collection includes his correspondence, sheet music, film, audio and video recordings.
